        <num>43-38-8</num>
        <content>
          <p>Notwithstanding any other provisions of this chapter, any person or corporation may use temporary employees for special events, provided that such temporary employment does not exceed 30 days in a calendar year and such employees do not carry firearms in connection with such employment.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1973, p. 40, ยง 9; Ga. L. 1981, p. 1828, ยง 7A; Ga. L. 1987, p. 1400, ยง 8.)</p>
